{
  "video_id": "ZHTLLUKYLkc",
  "title": "Why We Eat Oysters Alive",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 10777.0,
      "end_time": 15777.0,
      "text": "(instrumental music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16490.0,
      "end_time": 19150.0,
      "text": "- [Narrator] Most people think it's a food safety issue."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19150.0,
      "end_time": 21651.0,
      "text": "You keep the oyster alive as long as possible"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21651.0,
      "end_time": 25420.0,
      "text": "and that reduces the risk of bacterial contamination,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25420.0,
      "end_time": 27760.0,
      "text": "and there is a little bit of truth to that."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 27760.0,
      "end_time": 31300.0,
      "text": "Oysters can carry a scary flesh-eating bacteria called"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31300.0,
      "end_time": 33200.0,
      "text": "Vibrio vulnificus."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33200.0,
      "end_time": 34390.0,
      "text": "You can get it from oysters"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 34390.0,
      "end_time": 38800.0,
      "text": "or from swimming with an open wound in brackish water"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 38800.0,
      "end_time": 39940.0,
      "text": "where the bacteria lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 39940.0,
      "end_time": 42330.0,
      "text": "But, let's put things in prospective."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 42330.0,
      "end_time": 46810.0,
      "text": "- The risk of running into a bad oyster is phenomenally low."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46810.0,
      "end_time": 48830.0,
      "text": "My biggest pet peeve is people like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 48830.0,
      "end_time": 51660.0,
      "text": "go crazy over one bad oyster in the news,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 51660.0,
      "end_time": 53879.0,
      "text": "but they don't really care that hundreds of thousands"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53880.0,
      "end_time": 57110.0,
      "text": "of pounds of lettuce are contaminated with Salmonella."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 57110.0,
      "end_time": 58380.0,
      "text": "- [Narrator] About 100 people die"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 58380.0,
      "end_time": 60819.0,
      "text": "from Vibrio infections each year."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 60819.0,
      "end_time": 65480.0,
      "text": "About 450 die from Salmonella."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 65480.00000000001,
      "end_time": 69330.0,
      "text": "Plus, the FDA requires that oyster farm have to test"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 69330.0,
      "end_time": 71539.0,
      "text": "water quality before sending oysters"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 71540.0,
      "end_time": 73420.0,
      "text": "out to markets and restaurants,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 73420.0,
      "end_time": 78140.0,
      "text": "and that's important because oysters are filter feeders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 78140.0,
      "end_time": 81470.0,
      "text": "they soak basically anything that's in the water around them"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 81470.0,
      "end_time": 85640.0,
      "text": "including fecal matter which can come from rain runoff."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 85640.0,
      "end_time": 89460.0,
      "text": "Yak, but there's a clever little secret way you can check"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 89460.0,
      "end_time": 91339.0,
      "text": "how fresh your oysters are."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 91340.0,
      "end_time": 95300.0,
      "text": "- One thing that you can ask for is a shellfish tag,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 95300.0,
      "end_time": 98546.0,
      "text": "which every, retailer or restaurant is required to have"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 98546.0,
      "end_time": 102120.0,
      "text": "every bag of oyster that they purchase for up to 90 days,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 102120.0,
      "end_time": 106320.0,
      "text": "after that purchase. So, that tag, if they don't have it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 106320.0,
      "end_time": 107669.0,
      "text": "don't eat those oysters."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 107670.0,
      "end_time": 109390.0,
      "text": "- [Narrator] This tag is a way for restaurant"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 109390.0,
      "end_time": 113390.0,
      "text": "to track where and when the oysters were farmed."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 113390.0,
      "end_time": 116200.0,
      "text": "Qiu says that she looks for the most recent dates"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 116200.0,
      "end_time": 119190.0,
      "text": "on the tag, anything further out than two weeks"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 119190.0,
      "end_time": 122210.0,
      "text": "won't taste this good, and increases the risk"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 122210.0,
      "end_time": 123630.0,
      "text": "of a bad oyster."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 123630.0,
      "end_time": 125119.0,
      "text": "Some chefs may look at you funny"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 125120.0,
      "end_time": 127110.0,
      "text": "for asking for this documentation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 127110.0,
      "end_time": 130150.0,
      "text": "but it's a strategy that apparently works."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 130150.0,
      "end_time": 133260.0,
      "text": "- I tried to do the math and I probably had"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 133260.0,
      "end_time": 138260.0,
      "text": "over six or seven thousand oysters by now in my lifetime"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 138240.0,
      "end_time": 141700.0,
      "text": "and I've never gotten sick once from an oyster."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 141700.0,
      "end_time": 143829.0,
      "text": "- [Narrator] Basically, oysters are safe."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 143830.0,
      "end_time": 147953.0,
      "text": "So, question, why on earth are they still sometimes alive"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 147953.0,
      "end_time": 150980.0,
      "text": "or dying when we're eating them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 150980.0,
      "end_time": 154450.0,
      "text": "- You really want you're raw shellfish to be"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 154450.0,
      "end_time": 159450.0,
      "text": "absolutely fresh and, you know, the freshest you can get"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 159520.0,
      "end_time": 162980.0,
      "text": "is something that is just very recently killed."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 162980.0,
      "end_time": 167239.0,
      "text": "So, it goes back to not only the food safety"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 167240.0,
      "end_time": 170550.0,
      "text": "but the actual taste and the texture of that oyster"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 170550.0,
      "end_time": 172640.0,
      "text": "to me just far superior."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 172640.0,
      "end_time": 174739.0,
      "text": "- [Narrator] So, basically freshly killed oysters"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 174740.0,
      "end_time": 178300.0,
      "text": "taste better, and it's hard to tell exactly"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 178300.0,
      "end_time": 183300.0,
      "text": "when an oyster dies, because before it's served it's shocked"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 183180.0,
      "end_time": 186700.0,
      "text": "and shocking is, how should I put this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 186700.0,
      "end_time": 189390.0,
      "text": "shocking is not a gentle process."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 189390.0,
      "end_time": 192700.0,
      "text": "Shocking involves separating the oyster abductor muscle"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 192700.0,
      "end_time": 198510.0,
      "text": "form its shell, this muscle gives the oyster control over opening and closing the shell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 198710.0,
      "end_time": 202460.0,
      "text": "similar to how your spinal cord helps you move."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 202460.0,
      "end_time": 206180.0,
      "text": "So, severing their abductor muscle is almost like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 206180.0,
      "end_time": 209780.0,
      "text": "severing you spine. Yikes!"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 209780.0,
      "end_time": 213200.0,
      "text": "Most restaurants in the US keep their oysters alive on ice"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 213200.0,
      "end_time": 217859.0,
      "text": "up until the shocking process, which either kills the oyster"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 217860.0,
      "end_time": 220880.0,
      "text": "or renders it completely immobile."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 220880.0,
      "end_time": 223400.0,
      "text": "Since they don't move around much in the first place"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 223400.0,
      "end_time": 224822.0,
      "text": "it's kind of hard to tell which."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 225760.0,
      "end_time": 228769.0,
      "text": "So it's easy to feel guilty sitting there, eating an oyster"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 228770.0,
      "end_time": 232363.0,
      "text": "that was either just killed or is maybe dying."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 236700.0,
      "end_time": 238250.0,
      "text": "But consider the oyster biology."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 238250.0,
      "end_time": 240920.0,
      "text": "It's very primitive, so it's possible"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 240920.0,
      "end_time": 243700.0,
      "text": "they might not even feel pain at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 243700.0,
      "end_time": 244470.0,
      "text": "- [Julie Qiu] They don't have a brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 244470.0,
      "end_time": 246870.0,
      "text": "they're not really processing pain in the same way"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 246870.0,
      "end_time": 250220.0,
      "text": "that we process, any kind of feeling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 250220.0,
      "end_time": 254250.0,
      "text": "so, I don't believe that they are feeling pain"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 254250.0,
      "end_time": 256120.0,
      "text": "in the same way that we are thinking of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 256120.0,
      "end_time": 258587.0,
      "text": "- [Narrator] So, really it's a up to you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 258587.0,
      "end_time": 260899.0,
      "text": "if you don't wanna eat oyster, that's fine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 260899.0,
      "end_time": 264150.0,
      "text": "and if you do you won't be the first."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 264150.0,
      "end_time": 268169.0,
      "text": "- It's one of the few foods that have not changed in like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 268170.0,
      "end_time": 270420.0,
      "text": "thousands and thousands of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 270420.0,
      "end_time": 273640.0,
      "text": "So, being able to appreciate a food that has remained"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 273640.0,
      "end_time": 277700.0,
      "text": "unchanged for that long is something really special"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 277700.0,
      "end_time": 279900.0,
      "text": "and remarkable and I think it should be celebrated"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 279900.0,
      "end_time": 280614.0,
      "text": "for what it is."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 280614.0,
      "end_time": 285614.0,
      "text": "(instrumental music)"
    }
  ]
}